 days. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Creating meaningful relationships is often about sharing our lives with others, and technology can allow us to do so through photos, videos, text, and music.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unfortunately it has become part of human nature to look out for number 1 before considering others. Greed and self importance is prevalent in many societies, especially when it comes to business and politics. I believe that underneath this in every person there is the hidden truth that is much more harmonious. </span>','Impacts of Social Media on Relationships','','draft','open','open','','','','','2017-06-12 02:47:59','2017-06-12 02:47:59','',0,'http://nomads.digitalvillage.network/?p=163',0,'post','',0),(164,1,'2017-06-12 02:47:59','2017-06-12 02:47:59','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NOTES</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In such a noisy world these days we use the internet to filter and search for the things that are most suited to us. We </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instead, social relationships are being reconstructed on the basis of individual interests, values, and projects. Community is formed through individuals’ quests for like-minded people in a process that combines online interaction with offline interaction, cyberspace, and the local space.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Social media Websites have been found to be an avenue for people to display their narcissistic traits online (Buffardi &amp; Campbell, 2008). It seems common that people use social media to display their popularity or a false representaion of themesleves to increase their popularity to the world rather than use them as a vehicle to develop meaningful relationships. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Th